# apps/admin local dev (admin-foundation slice).
#
# Only DATABASE_URL is needed to run the tracer locally. It MUST point at the
# same master Postgres that apps/web uses — that's where the better-auth
# `sessions`/`users` rows live, so the staff gate can validate your session.
# Copy the value from apps/web/.env (the DATABASE_URL line) verbatim.
#
# `pnpm --filter @baseout/admin dev` renders this into the Hyperdrive
# localConnectionString in wrangler.jsonc, then runs `astro dev` on
# http://baseout.local:4332. (SSR runs in workerd, so the DB is reached via the
# Hyperdrive binding — the same way apps/web does it — not a direct connection.)
DATABASE_URL=

# Where the customer app (apps/web) serves its login. The admin console has no
# login of its own — unauthenticated visitors are routed here to sign in.
# Optional; defaults to the canonical local dev origin below.
# WEB_APP_URL=https://baseout.local:4331
